dataIdInfo.idAbs: This tool identifies each sink (i.e. topographic depression) in a raster digital elevation model (DEM). A sink, or depression, is a bowl-like landscape feature, which is characterized by interior drainage. Each identified sink in the input DEM is assigned a unique, non-zero, positive value in the ouput raster.

tool.name: Sink

param.name: output
param.dialogReference: The output raster. Output format is a float 32bit TIF file.

param.name: zero_background
param.displayname: Should a background value of zero be used?
param.dialogReference: Flag indicating whether a background value of zero should be used. If left unchecked background value will be NODATA.
